Sometimes the questions about the second plural could be a little misleading. For instance some bisyllabic words contained both of the vowels that were presented as choices, just in different parts of the word.
Asking me to choose if something sounded like boss or bass is tricky -- I saw 'bawss', my friends say 'baass', and I don't know if you mean bass guitar or bass fish.
It was an interesting exercise.  I'd like to do another exercise like this to try to get a better handle on which plurals sound more natural to which vowel and consonant combinations.
